<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">
Male: A medium sized 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphecodes" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">Sphecodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (6-8 mm) (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F6661800" captionText="Figure 5. Sphecodes majalis (Perez, 1903) (Manternach, specimen MNHNL 100057; BOLD identifier MNHNL 163 - 21, one middle leg was used for DNA extraction). a. Dorsal view; b. Lateral view; c. Antenna, showing flagellar segments; d. Left hind tibia, showing spines in pale pubescence; e. Tergites 4 and 5; f. Genitalia. Photos: MNHNL. Background edited using GIMP 2.8.22 (The GIMP Development Team 2020)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e64027.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/501351" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">5</figureCitation>
a and b). Flagellar segments of the antenna longer than broad, without pubescence in the front side (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F6661800" captionText="Figure 5. Sphecodes majalis (Perez, 1903) (Manternach, specimen MNHNL 100057; BOLD identifier MNHNL 163 - 21, one middle leg was used for DNA extraction). a. Dorsal view; b. Lateral view; c. Antenna, showing flagellar segments; d. Left hind tibia, showing spines in pale pubescence; e. Tergites 4 and 5; f. Genitalia. Photos: MNHNL. Background edited using GIMP 2.8.22 (The GIMP Development Team 2020)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e64027.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/501351" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">5</figureCitation>
c). The hind tibia present red spines on its upper side amongst a covering of pale hairs (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F6661800" captionText="Figure 5. Sphecodes majalis (Perez, 1903) (Manternach, specimen MNHNL 100057; BOLD identifier MNHNL 163 - 21, one middle leg was used for DNA extraction). a. Dorsal view; b. Lateral view; c. Antenna, showing flagellar segments; d. Left hind tibia, showing spines in pale pubescence; e. Tergites 4 and 5; f. Genitalia. Photos: MNHNL. Background edited using GIMP 2.8.22 (The GIMP Development Team 2020)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e64027.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/501351" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">5</figureCitation>
d). The punctures on tergites 4 and 5 are subtle and very sparsely distributed, presenting fine sculpture amongst them (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F6661800" captionText="Figure 5. Sphecodes majalis (Perez, 1903) (Manternach, specimen MNHNL 100057; BOLD identifier MNHNL 163 - 21, one middle leg was used for DNA extraction). a. Dorsal view; b. Lateral view; c. Antenna, showing flagellar segments; d. Left hind tibia, showing spines in pale pubescence; e. Tergites 4 and 5; f. Genitalia. Photos: MNHNL. Background edited using GIMP 2.8.22 (The GIMP Development Team 2020)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e64027.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/501351" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">5</figureCitation>
e). The gonocoxites lack any impression and the gonostyli have a rounded edge (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F6661800" captionText="Figure 5. Sphecodes majalis (Perez, 1903) (Manternach, specimen MNHNL 100057; BOLD identifier MNHNL 163 - 21, one middle leg was used for DNA extraction). a. Dorsal view; b. Lateral view; c. Antenna, showing flagellar segments; d. Left hind tibia, showing spines in pale pubescence; e. Tergites 4 and 5; f. Genitalia. Photos: MNHNL. Background edited using GIMP 2.8.22 (The GIMP Development Team 2020)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e64027.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/501351" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">5</figureCitation>
f).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">Voucher specimen (MNHNL100057; BOLD identifier MNHNL163-21): Adult male. Body length of 7.19 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" type="molecular identification">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">Molecular identification</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">
The taxonomic annotation is supported by DNA barcoding data. A perfect match of genetic sequence similarity was achieved with a specimen of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Perez" baseAuthorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphecodes majalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="majalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">Sphecodes majalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from France (100%; BOLD identifier POLLE1165-19), collected in Loir et Cher.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">Ecology</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">
A rare cuckoo bee that inhabits steppes and sunny sites, flying only during a short time span in spring from late March until mid-May, matching the flight season of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Brullé" baseAuthorityYear="1832" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lasioglossum pallens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">Lasioglossum pallens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Brullé">Brulle</normalizedToken>
, 1832), its only known host in Europe (
<bibRefCitation author="Amiet, F." journalOrPublisher="Fauna Helvetica 20. Apidae 5: Ammobates, Ammobatoides, Anthophora, Biastes, Ceratina, Dasypoda, Epeoloides, Epeolus, Eucera, Macropis, Melecta, Melitta, Nomada, Pasites, Tetralonia, Thyreus, Xylocopa." pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" refId="B6643129" refString="Amiet, F., Herrmann, M., Mueller, A, Neumeyer, R., 2007. . Fauna Helvetica 20. Apidae 5: Ammobates, Ammobatoides, Anthophora, Biastes, Ceratina, Dasypoda, Epeoloides, Epeolus, Eucera, Macropis, Melecta, Melitta, Nomada, Pasites, Tetralonia, Thyreus, Xylocopa. 5" volume="5" year="2007">Amiet et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bogusch, PETR" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" pagination="1 - 41" refId="B6643137" refString="Bogusch, PETR, Straka, JAKUB, 2012. Review and identification of the cuckoo bees of central Europe (Hymenoptera: Halictidae: Sphecodes). Zootaxa 3311 (1): 1 - 41" title="Review and identification of the cuckoo bees of central Europe (Hymenoptera: Halictidae: Sphecodes)" volume="3311" year="2012">Bogusch and Straka 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" type="conservation">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">Conservation</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Perez" baseAuthorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphecodes majalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="majalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">Sphecodes majalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is classified as &quot;Near Threatened (NT)&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="Nieto, A." journalOrPublisher="Luxembourg: Publications Office of the European Union" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" refId="B6643307" refString="Nieto, A., Roberts, S. P.M., Kemp, J., Rasmont, P., Kuhlmann, M., Garcia Criado, M., Biesmeijer, J. C., Bogusch, P., Dathe, H. H., De la Rua, P., De Meulemeester, T., Dehon, M., Dewulf, A., Ortiz-Sanchez, F. J., Lhomme, P., Pauly, A., Potts, S. G., Praz, C., Quaranta, M., Radchenko, V. G., Scheuchl, E., Smit, J., Straka, J., Terzo, M., Tomozii, B., Window, J., Michez, D., 2014. European Red List of bees. Luxembourg: Publications Office of the European Union" title="European Red List of bees" year="2014">Nieto et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
). Records of this bee and its host are scarce and the populations of both are described as locally decreasing (
<bibRefCitation author="Bogusch, PETR" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" refId="B6643146" refString="Bogusch P. Straka J. Sphecodes majalis. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2014 https://www.iucnredlist.org/species/19198950/21148788 2020-12-17T00:00:00+02:00" year="2012">Bogusch and Straka 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
